The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Tuesday, April 22, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Tuesday, April 22, 2003				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Paharpur Road. A stretch will be closed to allow sewerage repairs.				 																																	AJC Bose Road, in front of Calcutta Club and Rabindra Sadan. A flyover is coming up.				 																Earth Day				 																																	The need for cleaning the Maidan, a programme organised by People United for Better Living in Calcutta to mark Earth Day, in front of the Fountain of Joy, opposite Victoria Memorial, from 3 pm to 5 pm. Schoolchildren and environment activists will participate.				 																Crafts				 																																	Temptations Plus 2003, an exhibition featuring jewellery from Jaipur, German silver artefacts, murals and other items, presented by Inner Wheel Club of Central Calcutta, at Ice Skating Rink. Usha Uthup to inaugurate at 10.30 am.				 																																	A display of designerwear, Rajasthani handicrafts and stained glass items at Identity Gallery, Ballygunge, 10 am to 7 pm.				 																Sari display				 																																	An exhibition-cum-sale of saris and dress materials from across the country at Central Cottage Industries Emporium from 10 am to 7 pm.				 																Posters				 																																	50 years of French Posters (from 1940 to 2000) on display at Birla Academy of Art and Culture.				 																Art watch				 																																	An exhibition of paintings by women artists of Gond and Bhil tribes, presented by Srijan, at Sriniketan Art Gallery in Sodepur.
